The Kenya National Highways Authority (Kenha) has a warned of traffic congestion due to the scheduled closure of the Gilgil Weighbridge along Nairobi-Naivasha- Nakuru Highway. In a notice on Friday, Kenha said the disruption will occur from Saturday at 10.00pm to Monday 4.00pm to allow demolition of the old toll station at the weighbridge. "All vehicles shall be allowed to pass through the weighbridges on both directions to allow smooth traffic flow under the guidance of traffic police," the Authority said Motorists have been urged to use alternative routes to avoid possible congestion at the Njabini flyover near Soko Mjinga as well as Lanet -Dundori road.